
            <!-- Server Creation - Node Js & Express -->


            <!-- Basic Commands -->
            

        1. Create package.jason -npm init

        2. Install Express - npm i Express

        3. SErver run - nodemon index.js

        4. Inatall JWT Token - npm i jsonwebtoken

        5. Install mongoose - npm i mongoose

        6. Install CORS - npm i cors


            <!-- Basic step -->


        1. Create a Folder for Server
        2. Create package.jason
        3. Install Express
        4. Create Index.Js
        5. Import Express
        6. Create Server app Using Express
        7. Set up port number for Server
        8. HTTP Request resolving
        9. Run server
        10. Responce code

            1** - Information
            2** - Sucess
            3** - Redirection
            4** - Client error
            5** - Server error


        11. JWT Token - Json Wen Token

            => Token Generation  -  sign()
             => Token Validation  - verify() 


        12. Middleware

            => Application specific Middleware

            => Router specific Middleware



        13. Data base Integration - mongose

                => import mongoose
                => Connect the db using mangoose
                =>Create the model using mongoose

        
        14. resolve asynchronus - promise

                => resolve state - then()
                => reject state  - catch()

        15. CORS orgin resorce sharing

            